---
import SidebarLayout from '../../../layouts/SidebarLayout.astro';
import "../../../styles/global.css";
---

<SidebarLayout app="css">
  <h1 class="text-xl sm:text-3xl font-bold mb-5 text-custom-accent text-center">
    Filters & Blend Modes
  </h1>

  <section class="mb-5 space-y-6 text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed text-custom-secondary">
    <p>
      CSS filters and blend modes allow you to apply visual effects to elements, similar to image editing software. They can create stunning visual effects without needing image manipulation.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-custom-accent mt-6 mb-3">CSS Filters</h2>

    <div class="bg-custom-secondary border border-custom rounded-lg p-3 sm:p-4 my-4">
      <pre class="text-xs sm:text-sm overflow-x-auto whitespace-pre-wrap"><code>{`.image {
  /* Blur effect */
  filter: blur(5px);
  
  /* Brightness adjustment */
  filter: brightness(150%); /* brighter */
  filter: brightness(50%); /* darker */
  
  /* Contrast adjustment */
  filter: contrast(200%);
  
  /* Grayscale */
  filter: grayscale(100%); /* full grayscale */
  filter: grayscale(0.5); /* 50% grayscale */
  
  /* Hue rotation */
  filter: hue-rotate(90deg);
  
  /* Invert colors */
  filter: invert(100%);
  
  /* Opacity */
  filter: opacity(0.5);
  
  /* Saturate */
  filter: saturate(200%);
  
  /* Sepia */
  filter: sepia(100%);
  
  /* Drop shadow */
  filter: drop-shadow(5px 5px 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.5));
  
  /* Multiple filters */
  filter: brightness(1.2) contrast(1.1) saturate(1.1);
}`}</code></pre>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-custom-accent mt-6 mb-3">Blend Modes</h2>

    <div class="bg-custom-secondary border border-custom rounded-lg p-3 sm:p-4 my-4">
      <pre class="text-xs sm:text-sm overflow-x-auto whitespace-pre-wrap"><code>{`/* Background blend modes */
.element {
  background-image: 
    linear-gradient(45deg, blue, red),
    url('pattern.png');
  background-blend-mode: multiply;
}

/* Mix blend mode - blends element with content behind it */
.text {
  color: white;
  mix-blend-mode: difference;
}

/* Common blend modes */
.overlay { mix-blend-mode: overlay; }
.multiply { mix-blend-mode: multiply; }
.screen { mix-blend-mode: screen; }
.darken { mix-blend-mode: darken; }
.lighten { mix-blend-mode: lighten; }
.color-dodge { mix-blend-mode: color-dodge; }
.color-burn { mix-blend-mode: color-burn; }
.hard-light { mix-blend-mode: hard-light; }
.soft-light { mix-blend-mode: soft-light; }
.difference { mix-blend-mode: difference; }
.exclusion { mix-blend-mode: exclusion; }
.hue { mix-blend-mode: hue; }
.saturation { mix-blend-mode: saturation; }
.color { mix-blend-mode: color; }
.luminosity { mix-blend-mode: luminosity; }`}</code></pre>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-custom-secondary border border-custom rounded-2xl p-4 sm:p-6 mt-6">
      <h2 class="text-xl sm:text-2xl font-semibold text-custom-accent mb-3">Creative Applications</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 pl-4">
        <li><strong class="text-custom-primary">Image effects</strong>: Create photo filters with CSS</li>
        <li><strong class="text-custom-primary">Text effects</strong>: Use blend modes for creative typography</li>
        <li><strong class="text-custom-primary">Overlays</strong>: Create color overlays with blend modes</li>
        <li><strong class="text-custom-primary">Performance</strong>: Filters can be GPU-accelerated</li>
        <li><strong class="text-custom-primary">Accessibility</strong>: Ensure sufficient contrast when using filters</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</SidebarLayout>